Making Slideshows and Visualizations

Freemake Video Converter allows you to assemble still pictures into a slideshow. The end result is a video file you can play back as an animated slideshow.

Collecting Images

If you don't already have the images you want to include in your slideshow, you can download them from the web using Google Image Search. Add your search term to the end of this URL and paste it in your browser: http://google.com/search?tbm=isch&q=

Tip

It’s likely that the images you find on the web will be different sizes. Freemake Video Converter will automatically resize them so they’re all the same size for your slideshow. See Sizing Images, below.

  1. Search for your images
    Use an image search like the one described above.
  2. Click on an image you want to use in your slideshow. The image will become enlarged for you to preview.
  3. Right-click the image and select Save Picture As…
  4. Choose a folder on your computer where you would like to save the image.

Sizing Images

Even though the digital images you've collected may be different sizes, Freemake will automatically adjust images so they're all the same height when they appear in your slideshow.

Adding images to a slideshow

  1. To add your first photo to your slideshow, click the +Photo button at the top of the page. Now you can choose an image file to add to your slideshow.
  2. Browse to the directory where your images are saved, then click an image and click Open. The image will be added to your slideshow.
  3. Repeat these steps for each photo you want to add to your slideshow.

Adding audio to a slideshow

  1. Click the Play Slideshow icon on the right side of the page.

    The Photo Slideshow window appears.
  2. At the bottom of the window, you'll see the text "Audio track none." Click "none" and select "Browse…" from the contextual menu that appears. Now you can choose an audio file to add to your slideshow.
  3. Browse to the directory where your audio file is saved, then click the file name and click Open.
  4. Click the OK button in the bottom-right of the Photo Slideshow window.
  5. Back in the main window, the name of your audio file now appears in your slideshow description.
  6. To play your slideshow and hear the audio you added, click the Play Slideshow icon on the right side of the page.

Adding visualizations to an audio file

Freemake also allows you to add a visualization to an audio file. You can choose from a number of interesting animations to add visual appeal to your audio file. The result is an animated video file that combines the music and the visualization.
  1. Click the +Audio button at the top of the page. Now you can choose an audio file to add to your visualization.
  2. Browse to the directory where your audio file is saved, then click the file name and click Open.
  3. Click the Play Audio icon on the right side of the page.

    The Audio Playback window will appear.
  4. Click the Pinwheel button at the bottom of the window.

    Thumbnails of the available visualizations will appear.
  5. Click on the thumbnail of the visualization you want to add to your slideshow, then click OK.
  6. Play your file to hear the audio and watch the visualization: Click the Play Slideshow icon on the right side of the page.

Saving your slideshow

  1. Choose the file format you want to save to, and click the corresponding button at the bottom of the window. Scroll left or right to see more buttons.

    Tip

    For information on which video formats are suitable for various uses, see the Video Files and Formats section in this guide.
  2. Click save and name your file.
